have that anonymous class, so I should delete it. However, replacing it with `SiteRendererTest` brings in a new class for the public `SiteRenderer`. If there’s dynamic access for `SiteRenderer`, that’s fine, but if not, it feels extra. I’m not entirely sure about this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Thinking about Java and Groovy imports**\\n\\nI’m realizing that in Java and Groovy, I always need to import classes and use them without qualified names. That's a good practice! I could use something like `Files.new...` once it's imported. I shouldn’t need to compile just yet, but I might want to mention that I cannot run it now. It could be useful to inspect the git diff for any changes too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nCnrXQ9INoPudyCG4qSR5YIE|fc_0ddd3166638f72e8016a257d56dbb48197b9833db6d6ca4471", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-site-renderer/2.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven_doxia/doxia_site_renderer/DefaultSiteRendererTest.java tests/src/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-site-renderer/2.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven_doxia/doxia_site_renderer/SkinResourceLoaderTest.java tests/src/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-site-renderer/2.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven_doxia/doxia_site_renderer/RendererAnonymous1Test.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 892, "output": 1979, "cacheRead": 51712, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54583, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780841773311, "responseId": "resp_0ddd3166638f72e8016a257d2dff208197bc49e872d6eaff15"}}
